<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Bombing_of_Dresden_in_World_War_II&amp;action=edit&amp;section=26" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h2>
<div class="references-small references-column-count references-column-count-2" style="-moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> This was one of 16 figures surrounding the city hall tower, each representing a different virtue, such as "truth," "justice," and "sacrifice." The tower apparently survived all World War II bombings, but was later rebuilt, with the figures retained. <a href="http://www.dresden-lexikon.de/Lexikon-en/R.htm#Rathaus-2" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.dresden-lexikon.de/Lexikon-en/R.htm#Rathaus-2" rel="nofollow">[1]</a><a href="http://www.andreas-rosenthal.de/deutsch/aktuelles/angesichtsderguete/angesichtsderguete" class="external text" title="http://www.andreas-rosenthal.de/deutsch/aktuelles/angesichtsderguete/angesichtsderguete" rel="nofollow">001.html</a><a href="http://www.andreas-rosenthal.de/deutsch/aktuelles/angesichtsderguete/angesichtsderguete" class="external text" title="http://www.andreas-rosenthal.de/deutsch/aktuelles/angesichtsderguete/angesichtsderguete" rel="nofollow">002.html</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.spiegel.de/flash/0,5532,10589,00.html" class="external text" title="http://www.spiegel.de/flash/0,5532,10589,00.html" rel="nofollow">Aerial views of the damage</a>, <i>Der Spiegel</i>, retrieved 10 January, 2008.</li>
<li>Angell (1953) The number of bombers and tonnage bombs in the lead are taken from a USAF document written in 1953 and classified secret until 1978. Also see Taylor (2005), front flap, which gives the figures 1,100 heavy bombers and 4,500 tons.</li>
<li>Burleigh, Michael. <a href="http://books.guardian.co.uk/reviews/history/0,6121,1142632,00.html" class="external text" title="http://books.guardian.co.uk/reviews/history/0,6121,1142632,00.html" rel="nofollow">"Mission accomplished"</a>, <i>The Guardian</i>, 7 February 2004.</li>
